President Trump and President Erdogan held a joint press conference at the White House, where they discussed the long-standing relationship between the United States and Turkey. They emphasized their shared commitment to fighting terrorism, particularly ISIS, and expressed support for each other's efforts in Syria. They also discussed the need to strengthen trade and commercial ties between the two countries. President Erdogan praised President Trump's recent election victory and expressed hope for expanded cooperation in the future. The press conference concluded with President Trump addressing questions about his recent meeting with the Russian Foreign Minister, stating that their focus was on fighting ISIS and expressing optimism for the future of the US-Turkey relationship.